comment: [Incidental or immaterial] Zeller (CHA) pushes Oubre (WAS) during the screen.
Gortat (WAS) makes contact with Zeller (CHA) that affects his SQBR.
Zeller (CHA) maintains legal guarding position and makes marginal contact with Wall (WAS) that does not affect his SQBR.
Zeller (CHA) maintains legal guarding position on the shot attempt by Oubre (WAS).
Batum (CHA) legally contests Oubre's (WAS) shot attempt and the contact is incidental.
Zeller (CHA) sets the screen on Beal (WAS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Wall (WAS) makes contact with Kidd-Gilchrist (CHA) that affects his SQBR.
Porter (WAS) sets the screen on Walker (CHA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Zeller (CHA) obtains a legal guarding position and jumps vertically to defend Wall's (WAS) driving shot attempt.
Zeller (CHA) sets the screen on Wall (WAS) and the two players briefly engage and separate.
Zeller (CHA) plants his foot and firms up, and the contact on the screen is to Porter's (WAS) chest.
Batum (CHA) makes body to body contact with Beal (WAS) that affects his SQBR.
Zeller (CHA) sets the screen on Beal (WAS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Belinelli (CHA) maintains legal guarding position on Wall (WAS), and Batum (CHA) cleanly makes contact with the ball.
Walker (CHA) commits a take foul on Wall (WAS).
Zeller (CHA) and Wall (WAS) briefly engage and separate away from the play.
Zeller (CHA) and Thornton (WAS) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Porter (WAS) legally contests Walker's (CHA) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
